section.section:
The report shall:
Include the information required under this subsection and any additional information concerning environmental enforcement that the Secretary decides to provide;
Be available to the public as soon as it is forwarded to the Legislative Policy Committee;
Include information on the total number of permits and licenses issued by or filed with the Department at any time and still in effect as of the last date of the fiscal year immediately preceding the date on which the report is filed;
Include information concerning specific enforcement actions taken with respect to the permits and licenses during the immediately preceding fiscal year; and
Include information on the type and number of contacts or consultations with businesses concerning compliance with State environmental laws.

The report shall state the total amount of money as a result of enforcement actions, as of the end of the immediately preceding fiscal year:
Deposited in the Maryland Clean Air Fund;
Deposited in the Maryland Oil Disaster Containment, Clean-Up and Contingency Fund;
Deposited in the Nontidal Wetland Compensation Fund;
Deposited in the Maryland Hazardous Substance Control Fund;
Recovered by the Department from responsible parties in accordance with § 7-221 of this article; and
Deposited in the Maryland Clean Water Fund.

The report shall include the information specified in subparagraphs (ii), (iii), (iv), and (v) of this paragraph for each of the following programs in the Department:
Ambient air quality control under Title 2, Subtitle 4 of this article;
Oil pollution under Title 4, Subtitle 4 of this article;
Nontidal wetlands under Title 5, Subtitle 9 of this article;
Asbestos under Title 6, Subtitle 4 of this article;
Lead paint under Title 6, Subtitle 8 of this article;
Controlled hazardous substances under Title 7, Subtitle 2 of this article;
Water supply, sewerage systems, and refuse disposal systems under Title 9, Subtitle 2 of this article;
Water discharges under Title 9, Subtitle 3 of this article;
Drinking water under Title 9, Subtitle 4 of this article; and
Wetlands under Title 16, Subtitle 2 of this article.

For each of the programs set forth in subparagraph (i) of this paragraph, the Department shall provide the total number or amount of:
Final permits or licenses issued to a person or facility, as appropriate, and not surrendered, suspended, or revoked;
Inspections, audits, or spot checks performed at facilities permitted;
Injunctions obtained;
Show cause, remedial, and corrective action orders issued;
Stop work orders;
Administrative or civil penalties obtained;
Criminal actions charged, convictions obtained, imprisonment time ordered, and criminal fines received; and
Any other actions taken by the Department to enforce the requirements of the applicable environmental program, including:
